00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:42,680
{\an8}3C Group… Let's see how I can crush you.

2
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,760
{\an8}If you tarnish my family's name,

3
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:48,520
{\an8}you won't get a single penny.

4
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:53,840
{\an8}I'll kill their members one by one
until I reach their ringleader.

5
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:03,360
{\an8}It's good to finally meet you, Taiga.

6
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:06,120
- I don't know you.
- But I know you very well.

7
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:08,520
You're not actually Mr. Kenji's son.

8
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:13,600
What are you, the son
of Blazing Tiger's yakuza boss,

9
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,960
doing at Cosmic Central Group?

10
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:20,160
I…

11
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:23,080
used to know your real parents.

12
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:28,560
And the one who saved you is me.

13
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:42,680
If you make Taiga the leader,

14
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:45,200
I think we'll run into problems.

15
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:48,560
Because he isn't my real son?

16
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:59,280
This orphan from Thailand

17
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:02,480
has grown up perfectly as my only son.

18
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:06,800
No matter his past, Taiga's future

19
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:10,080
will never let our Blazing Tiger crumble.

20
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,360
Prin, your father, is a good man.

21
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:44,320
As for me and your mother,

22
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,240
we were friends.

23
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:49,560
Your mother chose to marry your father.

24
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:56,600
I stepped in when I learned Fire Phoenix
was after your father.

25
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,560
Fire Phoenix eliminates anyone in its way.

26
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:03,880
When they killed Mr. Kenji,

27
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:05,960
you had to come to Thailand,

28
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:08,320
to Cosmic Central,

29
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:10,680
the place your father built.

30
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:13,760
But a treacherous friend
like Naruban seized everything

31
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:15,920
and destroyed your family.

32
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:00,120
Pok, don't.

33
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:03,040
Prae! It's me.

34
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:08,320
Dear.

35
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:20,080
Pok, take care of your mother
and brothers.

36
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,960
Dad, come with us.

37
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:23,400
I'll follow shortly.

38
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:27,080
You need to take the kids to Khanin.

39
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:29,080
He'll hide you and our children.

40
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:30,760
And you?

41
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:32,480
I'm exposing Fire Phoenix.

42
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,240
I won't sell them the satellite.

43
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,440
I won't let customer data

44
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:39,520
fall into Fire Phoenix's hands
as a terrorist tool.

45
00:06:43,960 --> 00:06:45,040
Let's go.

46
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,360
Hurry! Go!

47
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:55,720
Let's go.

48
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:04,680
Let's go.

49
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:09,840
- Hey!
- Hey!

50
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,520
- Oh no!
- Ugh!

51
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,240
- Dad!
- Dear!

52
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:19,440
Ugh.

53
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:22,000
Prae, I love you.

54
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,040
We'll wait for you, Prin.

55
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:36,320
Go, quickly.

56
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:38,120
Let's go.

57
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:39,280
Ugh.

58
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:43,280
Let's go, dear.

59
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,480
Go, quickly!

60
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:59,440
Pok, get out of here!

61
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:02,960
No!

62
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:05,600
Dad!

63
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,320
Hurry!

64
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:01,320
Get them!

65
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:03,680
Quick, Mom! They're coming!

66
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:06,440
Mom!

67
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:07,880
Mom!

68
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:10,960
Mom!

69
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:23,400
Ugh!

70
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:28,800
Hey.

71
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:52,960
Let's go.

72
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:23,360
I helped you first, Pok.

73
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:26,000
Then I helped your two younger brothers.

74
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:46,120
Dad. Mom!

75
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:02,720
By the time I came back,
you were already gone.

76
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:06,440
I searched for you everywhere for years.

77
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:12,680
I found out you stayed at a temple,
then a wealthy Japanese took you in.

78
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,480
All of you, leave!

79
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,800
He just came here to stay.

80
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,960
He can't answer questions properly

81
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:46,320
and doesn't even remember his own name.

82
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:49,000
We're trying to help him
find his relatives.

83
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:52,160
Seeing him reminds me of my son Hikaru.

84
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:57,080
If he's still alive, he'd be about
the same age as this little boy.

85
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:24,200
Do you want a home, kid?

86
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:32,000
Later, there was a police officer

87
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:34,320
handling your family's case.

88
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,760
He chased the four gunmen
who had fled the country

89
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,760
and did everything he could.
In the end, the case was called off,

90
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:45,080
without catching the mastermind
or any gunmen.

91
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:48,680
Where is he now?

92
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:56,440
Inspector Phumin died four years ago.

93
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:11,160
Fire Phoenix killed him.

94
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:13,240
I'm not sure.

95
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:17,880
He died when one of the gunmen reappeared.
It was Chok.

96
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:19,480
He had been missing for ten years.

97
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:30,960
Got the money?

98
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,680
Don't mess around.

99
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:34,920
Or I'll expose everything.

100
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:39,640
I know Prin's three sons are still alive.

101
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:50,960
Good.

102
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:28,920
I need to verify what you're saying.

103
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:32,800
Where is that police officer's family now?

104
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:37,000
The eldest daughter is abroad,
completely cut off from everything here.

105
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:39,960
As for the youngest…

106
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,080
Where's the youngest?

107
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,160
Drowned.

108
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:53,720
So you're saying
that everyone you mentioned,

109
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:56,120
all of them is dead.

110
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:00,720
Even the children you said was me

111
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:04,520
and my siblings. You have no proof.

112
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:07,000
Fire Phoenix never spares their enemies!

113
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:15,920
You don't have to believe me.

114
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,440
But I want you to know

115
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:22,160
I'm gathering all the evidence
that Inspector Phumin ever collected.

116
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:25,080
Your parents' deaths won't be in vain.

117
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:31,360
Naruban stole everything your father built
despite him being the original founder.

118
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:35,960
You know Naruban is tied to Fire Phoenix.

119
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:40,280
Since Mr. Kenji died, Cosmic Central Group

120
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:43,680
has been buying up every business
your father owned in Japan.

121
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:46,240
That's where they launder their money.

122
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:50,560
Mr. Kenji

123
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:53,640
protected you for years.

124
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:59,840
But eventually, Fire Phoenix found you.
That's why they spare no one.

125
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:02,960
Dad died because of me.

126
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:12,040
I want you to think it over for yourself.

127
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:14,080
If you believe me,

128
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:16,560
we'll hunt them together.

129
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:18,320
Even if they hide in the shadows,

130
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:21,080
Fire Phoenix must be exposed!

131
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:09,680
If there's no sun,
life would be impossible, huh?

132
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:13,040
Yeah.

133
00:17:13,119 --> 00:17:14,839
You can't be without me.

134
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:24,960
If you hurt Aru, you're dead.

135
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:31,040
Aru, she's scary. Help!

136
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:32,320
Come on.

137
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,800
Come here!

138
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:39,480
{\an8}Let's take a photo.

139
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:42,480
Come on!

140
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:45,960
- My bangs!
- Cheese!

141
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:47,120
Aw.

142
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,120
It's good now.

143
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:50,440
One, two, three!

144
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,760
So cute.

145
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:56,040
Why close your eyes?

146
00:17:56,120 --> 00:17:57,800
- Let's see the other shots.
- Adorable!

147
00:17:57,880 --> 00:18:00,120
Here, the other shots look fine.

148
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:02,080
- Yeah.
- Okay.

149
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:04,800
Aru.

150
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:09,200
If there's no sun, I'll be your sunshine.

151
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:26,000
Lee!

152
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,160
You're not dead.

153
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:32,440
My name's Rin.

154
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:50,240
You look just like my best friend,

155
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:53,320
really similar.

156
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,840
But no fangs.

157
00:18:57,960 --> 00:18:59,400
Your skin's different.

158
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:07,920
Lee is gone.

159
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:13,440
You helped me.

160
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:16,240
Yeah.

161
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:18,040
I pass by there every day.

162
00:19:18,560 --> 00:19:21,480
I helped, but didn't know where to go,
so I brought you here.

163
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:24,760
Thanks.

164
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:28,600
I'm Aru. I won't trouble you for long.

165
00:19:31,560 --> 00:19:33,880
I asked the building owner.

166
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:35,840
The last room down the hall is available.

167
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:40,200
Thanks, Rin.

168
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:43,240
Hungry?

169
00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:47,520
For you.

170
00:19:54,720 --> 00:19:55,880
Thank you.

171
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:14,600
Pol.Lt.Col. Phumin Pongrit!

172
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,040
Here's your medal.

173
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:38,920
What should a taekwondo champion

174
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,640
get as a reward?

175
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:44,000
You already got a new phone.

176
00:21:45,520 --> 00:21:49,840
Spare the poor cop. My wallet's
been through a lot already.

177
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,600
I'm just joking!

178
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:57,680
I'll claim it all at once when I graduate

179
00:21:57,760 --> 00:22:01,800
with first-class honors. How about a car?

180
00:22:03,040 --> 00:22:07,560
We'll settle it later when the time comes.
I'm a bit forgetful these days.

181
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:16,000
It's the same case, right?
It's been so many years.

182
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:19,920
Whole family wiped out,
father, mother, and three sons.

183
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:21,840
They were unbelievably cruel.

184
00:22:25,840 --> 00:22:29,560
I'll become a police officer
and continue your investigation.

185
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:33,200
Don't you want to be a national athlete?

186
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:34,320
I do.

187
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:36,800
I want to be both a national athlete
and a police officer.

188
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:38,640
That's the coolest!

189
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:42,960
Here.

190
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:33,240
This is for your report.

191
00:23:38,560 --> 00:23:39,680
Ugh!

192
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:41,720
Why is this so hard?

193
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,880
In Thailand,

194
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:47,720
- Transition metals are elements or ions
- they use Debt-to-GDP

195
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:49,440
- with outermost electrons.
- to assess…

196
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:50,880
To assess…

197
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:52,080
To assess…

198
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:54,960
- D-orbital.
- To assess…

199
00:23:55,040 --> 00:23:58,080
- Complex compounds.
- household debt.

200
00:23:58,160 --> 00:24:00,000
- Coordination compounds.
- Yet it's not

201
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:02,920
- Reactive to oxygen
- a true reflection

202
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:04,920
- in the air.
- of the economy.

203
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:07,200
What are you two doing?

204
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:11,840
Wait a minute.

205
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:14,520
Huh?

206
00:24:15,360 --> 00:24:19,480
That super-hot Professor Methee
just came over and talked to you.

207
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:23,280
No way!

208
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:25,720
Yes, I saw it too.

209
00:24:26,320 --> 00:24:28,560
Hey, are you going to tell us or not?

210
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:31,880
If you don't,
the whole university will know!

211
00:24:35,760 --> 00:24:38,720
Hey, hit him again. I allow it.

212
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:40,320
Hey.

213
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:43,480
You're always rough
with your boyfriend, seriously.

214
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:50,200
He's hitting on you, right?

215
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:52,120
He's not!

216
00:24:53,240 --> 00:24:55,760
- Nah, I'll continue reading.
- Hey.

217
00:24:55,840 --> 00:24:57,920
Suspicious.

218
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:59,080
Not suspicious!

219
00:24:59,160 --> 00:25:00,920
- Wow!
- Gotcha!

220
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:03,200
Come on, tell us.

221
00:25:11,240 --> 00:25:12,600
Lee.

222
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:16,240
Sorry, I came to return the book.

223
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:19,760
Go wait in the garden for a bit.
I'll take a quick shower.

224
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:23,680
That's fine. I'll just leave it here.

225
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:28,280
Who are you talking to?

226
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:30,880
Oh.

227
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:32,440
This is the person you called over?

228
00:25:34,120 --> 00:25:37,920
Lee, wait! It's not what you think!

229
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:53,920
Do you want to tell me anything?

230
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:08,960
I'm proud you're my daughter.

231
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:12,440
You take after your mom.

232
00:26:13,720 --> 00:26:16,240
Beautiful, kind,

233
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:19,000
and easy to get along with.

234
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:21,760
If your mom were here,

235
00:26:23,120 --> 00:26:25,120
she'd be just as happy as I am.

236
00:26:31,880 --> 00:26:33,800
I got fooled.

237
00:26:35,520 --> 00:26:36,600
Who fooled you?

238
00:26:40,760 --> 00:26:43,320
It's okay. I'll only be dumb once.

239
00:26:50,440 --> 00:26:52,160
I love you, Dad.

240
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:56,960
I'll study hard to become
a police officer like you.

241
00:27:06,840 --> 00:27:07,960
Come on!

242
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:10,440
Ugh! Are we done?

243
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:35,120
Dad, you deserve lots of stars
on your shoulders

244
00:27:35,720 --> 00:27:38,680
for all the hard work you do
helping people.

245
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:41,440
But I want all the stars in the sky

246
00:27:41,520 --> 00:27:43,120
to belong to you.

247
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:45,680
My angel.

248
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:49,560
When I graduate and get a job,

249
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:53,120
I'll take care of you
and make you the happiest.

250
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:55,680
Alright.

251
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:25,240
Dad!

252
00:28:31,680 --> 00:28:32,760
Dad, watch out!

253
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:36,360
Take cover!

254
00:28:54,360 --> 00:28:55,280
Are you okay, my dear?

255
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:04,800
Dad!

256
00:29:06,080 --> 00:29:07,120
Dad!

257
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:15,320
Dad…

258
00:29:33,840 --> 00:29:36,720
Do you know why your father was shot?

259
00:29:36,800 --> 00:29:37,760
Please answer.

260
00:29:37,840 --> 00:29:39,600
- Just answer us.
- Please tell us.

261
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:41,200
- Who let the reporters in?
- Say something.

262
00:29:43,200 --> 00:29:45,440
- Please give us the information.
- Get them out.

263
00:29:45,520 --> 00:29:47,160
Excuse me. Please leave.

264
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,280
Please step outside.

265
00:29:48,360 --> 00:29:51,440
Uncle Punlop! Who shot my father?

266
00:29:51,520 --> 00:29:55,960
We're tracking him down. Don't worry.
I won't let Phumin die in vain.

267
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:04,280
Is it true Inspector Phumin is linked
to a kidnapping and extortion gang?

268
00:30:04,360 --> 00:30:07,480
Is he also connected
to the suspect's secret drug accounts?

269
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:10,040
That's not true!

270
00:30:10,120 --> 00:30:14,360
My dad would never be involved
in something like that. He's a good man!

271
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:17,200
Lee, stay strong.

272
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:18,960
Stay strong.

273
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:20,560
Uncle.

274
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:25,560
Why are they asking things like that?
You know my dad would never take bribes.

275
00:30:26,280 --> 00:30:28,440
He wasn't a corrupt cop!

276
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:34,760
Alright.

277
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:03,280
<i>Uncle, what's Fire Phoenix?</i>

278
00:31:04,280 --> 00:31:05,520
Did Phumin tell you about this?

279
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:09,480
Dad never went into details.

280
00:31:10,320 --> 00:31:12,560
But I saw him keep all the information.

281
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:19,600
Bring those things to me.
You shouldn't be involved in this.

282
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:22,240
What's it about?

283
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:26,920
You were Dad's most trusted subordinate.

284
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:30,200
Please tell me.

285
00:31:36,040 --> 00:31:37,080
Fire Phoenix…

286
00:31:39,240 --> 00:31:41,320
is something a kid like you
shouldn't know about

287
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:43,080
or get involved in.

288
00:31:44,080 --> 00:31:45,640
But my dad's dead.

289
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:48,680
He spent his life working for others.

290
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:52,680
But everyone's criticizing him
because they believe the fake news.

291
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:58,240
I know we shouldn't think like this.

292
00:32:02,920 --> 00:32:05,160
But the law can't protect
every good person.

293
00:32:10,600 --> 00:32:14,800
Fire Phoenix
is a secret organization that works

294
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:17,400
to eliminate injustice in society.

295
00:32:18,840 --> 00:32:22,440
That means Fire Phoenix
can find who killed my father.

296
00:32:23,560 --> 00:32:26,200
Uncle, where is Fire Phoenix?

297
00:32:27,720 --> 00:32:28,880
No, Lee.

298
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:33,400
It's too dangerous.
Let the law handle this.

299
00:32:34,280 --> 00:32:37,880
But you said it yourself,
that the law can't always help.

300
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:41,240
How long will it take for everyone
to realize Dad wasn't a corrupt cop?

301
00:32:41,320 --> 00:32:45,480
Ten years? Twenty years?
Every time someone searches his name,

302
00:32:45,560 --> 00:32:49,520
they see bribe-taking cop, corrupt cop.

303
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:53,360
Just because the law
can't catch the real mastermind.

304
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:12,239
Search everywhere. She's here.

305
00:34:48,480 --> 00:34:49,719
Hah!

306
00:35:02,720 --> 00:35:03,720
Hey!

307
00:35:06,080 --> 00:35:07,240
Hey!

308
00:35:30,840 --> 00:35:31,960
Go.

309
00:35:41,520 --> 00:35:42,440
Yes, sir.

310
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:44,440
Got it.

311
00:35:46,640 --> 00:35:48,080
Boss said to kill her like her father.

312
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:50,440
Hah!

313
00:37:56,520 --> 00:37:57,560
Uncle.

314
00:38:01,240 --> 00:38:02,240
Lee!

315
00:38:03,880 --> 00:38:05,920
I'm going to find Fire Phoenix.

316
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:10,320
No, you can't, Lee.

317
00:38:10,840 --> 00:38:12,560
This time, you might not survive.

318
00:38:13,840 --> 00:38:16,160
Luckily, my people found you. Otherwise…

319
00:38:25,120 --> 00:38:26,720
If you want Fire Phoenix to help…

320
00:38:30,120 --> 00:38:33,760
There will be a price.
Think carefully, Lee.

321
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:37,240
Once you take this path,

322
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:40,240
there's no turning back.

323
00:39:01,640 --> 00:39:03,840
You can take my life if you want.

324
00:41:25,520 --> 00:41:28,280
From now on, Lee doesn't exist
in this world anymore.

325
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:49,520
Can I see my friend's face one last time?

326
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:52,840
You can't tell
what she looked like anymore.

327
00:41:52,920 --> 00:41:55,480
She drowned, rotted, and was eaten
by animals. Only bones remain.

328
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:58,880
She's probably been dead for months.

329
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:03,920
The only ID we found
is under the name Ms. Lirin Pongrit.

330
00:42:11,080 --> 00:42:12,480
Lee…

331
00:42:13,880 --> 00:42:17,720
Sun, why did she have to die like this?

332
00:42:34,680 --> 00:42:35,920
Here you go.

333
00:42:36,520 --> 00:42:37,960
Thank you.

334
00:42:57,360 --> 00:42:58,320
Thanks.

335
00:43:03,280 --> 00:43:05,000
You're working like you owe someone money.

336
00:43:09,880 --> 00:43:11,320
Worse than that.

337
00:43:13,480 --> 00:43:18,560
I just got out of prison.

338
00:43:21,480 --> 00:43:24,520
Manslaughter case.

339
00:43:25,640 --> 00:43:29,560
The tickets are ready.
The ski clothes are ready.

340
00:43:30,320 --> 00:43:32,560
What's missing?

341
00:43:37,600 --> 00:43:39,440
The wedding ring is ready too.

342
00:43:41,360 --> 00:43:43,560
I'll propose to you in the snow.

343
00:43:49,080 --> 00:43:50,400
Hey, what the hell?

344
00:43:50,480 --> 00:43:51,760
Hey.

345
00:43:55,440 --> 00:43:56,720
- Ouch!
- Oh!

346
00:43:57,240 --> 00:43:59,400
Hey! What's your problem?

347
00:43:59,480 --> 00:44:00,600
Sorry.

348
00:44:00,680 --> 00:44:03,840
Nice wife you got there.
Can I borrow her for a night?

349
00:44:04,800 --> 00:44:05,760
She's cute.

350
00:44:06,280 --> 00:44:08,120
Sun!

351
00:44:08,200 --> 00:44:09,840
- Oh!
- Ugh!

352
00:44:15,560 --> 00:44:16,800
Sun, oh no!

353
00:44:23,200 --> 00:44:24,280
Sun!

354
00:44:25,920 --> 00:44:27,040
Let go!

355
00:44:28,120 --> 00:44:29,160
Huh?

356
00:44:33,320 --> 00:44:34,600
Hey! What's going on here?

357
00:44:34,680 --> 00:44:36,400
- Stop!
- Hey, the cops are here!

358
00:44:36,480 --> 00:44:37,440
Hurry up!

359
00:44:37,520 --> 00:44:38,440
{\an8}Police!

360
00:44:39,840 --> 00:44:40,880
Please come with us.

361
00:44:42,400 --> 00:44:44,600
Take care of your family, Sun.

362
00:44:53,880 --> 00:44:55,080
I confessed.

363
00:44:56,320 --> 00:44:58,280
Got a three-year sentence,

364
00:44:58,880 --> 00:45:01,800
but since I was a model prisoner,
served only two.

365
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:06,440
How's that for a profile?

366
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:09,480
Perfect.

367
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:18,440
Don't overthink it.
If you need anything, just ask.

368
00:45:34,240 --> 00:45:35,880
Come on, Aru.

369
00:45:35,960 --> 00:45:38,320
You're Arunothai.

370
00:45:40,080 --> 00:45:42,120
Time to start your new life.

371
00:45:49,200 --> 00:45:50,040
Oops.

372
00:45:56,480 --> 00:45:59,560
{\an8}The website Rin found
is related to Fire Phoenix.

373
00:45:59,640 --> 00:46:04,320
{\an8}Mr. Taiga's my personal designer.
He can work here

374
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:05,760
{\an8}anytime.

375
00:46:08,320 --> 00:46:09,920
{\an8}<i>Fire Phoenix…</i>

376
00:46:11,840 --> 00:46:14,200
{\an8}will pay with every life
for Blazing Tiger!

377
00:46:42,600 --> 00:46:46,760
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn

